gameSystems:
DASH (deliberate burst, distinct from hold-boost): Intent += dash:boolean (edge: Space keydown or touch #dash-button pointerdown; input.js latches one read). BallState += dashGauge01, dashTimer. ballPhysics.step: gauge += dt/DASH_RECHARGE_S and += DASH_ABSORB_GAIN per absorb (absorb.js one-liner, clamped at 1); when gauge first reaches 1 emit EVT.DASH_READY once (frame-accurate HUD ready-flash + soft chime); on intent.dash && gauge>=1: gauge=0, dashTimer=DASH_DURATION_S, vel += (velDir or camForward if stationary) * DASH_IMPULSE_K * radiusSim; while dashTimer>0: speedCap*=DASH_CAP_MUL, accel*=DASH_ACCEL_MUL; emits EVT.DASH (bus injected, null-safe headless). Feel: cameraRig adds DASH_FOV_BONUS kick decaying over DASH_DURATION_S (additive with v1 kick); effects speed-lines burst; sfx whoosh. Dashing into walls bonks (terrain EVT.BOUNCE) and knocks stuck objects off — risk/reward intact. Gauge is dimensionless: preserved across rescale. HUD FEED: GrowEvent += dashGauge01 (scaleManager reads ball state when emitting GROW at 10Hz) + EVT.DASH/DASH_READY edges — no laggy gauge. TIMER: src/game/runStats.js owns elapsed = accumulated fixed steps; main calls runStats.addSimTime(stepsTaken*FIXED_DT) per frame (deterministic, fps-independent, pauses with the state machine); starts on GAME_START, freezes at GOAL; emits EVT.TIME {timeS} at 10Hz for the HUD mm:ss.t. SCORE (on EVT.ABSORB): objScore = max(1, round(SCORE_SIZE_BASE * sizeReal^SCORE_SIZE_POW)); comboMul = min(1 + COMBO_SCORE_K*(combo-1), COMBO_SCORE_MAX_MUL); +RARE_SCORE_BONUS when rareProvider.isRare(objIndex); statue adds STATUE_SCORE. Emits EVT.SCORE {score,delta,combo,rare} -> HUD panel + floating '+N'. ABSORB HANDLER ORDER (documented in events.js header, asserted in dev): ball attach -> runStats -> levelSpawner -> chunk spawner; AND LevelSpawner is order-resilient anyway: its ABSORB handler only marks consumed and queues cleanup, executed on its NEXT update() tick, so FLAG_RARE/isRare stay valid through the whole emit. RARES: LevelSpawner sets FLAG_RARE(8)|FLAG_LEVEL(16) on its slots; exposes isRare(idx), forEachAliveRare(cb) (effects polls for golden sparkles), rareTotal; rare credit is granted at FIRST absorb and FLAG_RARE is stripped if the object is knocked off (no double count; knocked-off rares reinject as ordinary objects). STORE OWNERSHIP PROTOCOL (Phase-0 contract): chunk Spawner._onAbsorb early-returns on FLAG_LEVEL slots (no aliveCount/slotGen cross-talk); _subPixelSweep skips FLAG_LEVEL and FLAG_RARE (rares persist until absorbed or run end); LevelSpawner frees its own slots and runs its own small far-deactivate sweep; dev assert chunkAlive+levelAlive === storeAlive each second. GOAL FLOW: runStats sees ABSORB.archetypeId==='bronze_statue' -> freeze timer, rank = S<=240s / A<=330 / B<=450 / C<=600 / else D, persist best (only-improves) to localStorage LS_BEST_KEY {bestTimeS,bestScore,bestRank,seed}, emit EVT.GOAL once {timeS,score,rank,trueRadius,absorbed,raresFound,rareTotal,seed}. main.js: PLAYING -> CELEBRATE (input zeroed, physics still steps so the ball settles; cameraRig.celebrate() slow orbit pull-back; effects confetti; bgm ducks; sfx grand fanfare) -> after CELEBRATE_S emit GAME_WIN -> WIN state; screens shows RESULT (time, big rank letter, score, final size ~2.75m copy, absorbed count, レア x/6, best, seed). FAIRNESS: rng.js resolveWorldSeed default = DEFAULT_WORLD_SEED (fixed) instead of Date.now() (?seed= still overrides; seed shown on result; curated placements are seed-independent). X POST: #post-x-button click (user gesture, popup-safe): text = `🟡FABLE KATAMARI 完走！
⏱タイム ${mm:ss.t} / RANK ${rank}
⭐スコア ${score.toLocaleString()}
📏さいご ${sizeStr} / まきこんだ ${absorbed}こ / レア ${found}/${total}
#FableKatamari
https://fable-katamari.pages.dev`; window.open('https://x.com/intent/post?text='+encodeURIComponent(text),'_blank','noopener,noreferrer'). RESET/TELEPORT: BallPhysics.reset(radiusSim, x, z, standSimY) (main queries terrain — physics stays terrain-optional for headless tests); seeds _ySpring.value = standSimY+radiusSim, standSimY field set; ?at=house|garden|street|plaza reads DEV_STARTS from level.js: set worldScale/scaleExp via the existing ?r= machinery, ball reset at the authored point, force spawner band-cache invalidation + spawner.preload + levelSpawner.preload + one maybeRebase. DOOR HINT: on EVT.DOOR_HINT HUD shows 'おおきすぎる！' toast (3s cooldown).

